### ==========================================================
### Auth Service — 10 requests
### Flow: register → login → use token for authenticated calls
### ==========================================================

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5050
@accessToken = <paste-after-login>

### 1. Register a new user
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "username": "testuser",
  "password": "TestPassword123!",
  "displayName": "Test User"
}

### 2. Login
# Copy accessToken from the response and paste into @accessToken above
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "emailOrUsername": "test@example.com",
  "password": "TestPassword123!"
}

### 3. Refresh token
# For native clients: pass refreshToken in body
# For web clients: the HttpOnly cookie is sent automatically
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "<paste-refresh-token>"
}

### 4. Logout
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "<paste-refresh-token>"
}

### 5. Get profile
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 6. Update profile
PUT {{baseUrl}}/auth/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "displayName": "Updated Name",
  "avatarUrl": "https://example.com/avatar.png"
}

### 7. Change password
PUT {{baseUrl}}/auth/password
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "currentPassword": "TestPassword123!",
  "newPassword": "NewPassword456!"
}

### 8. Search users
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/users/search?q=test
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 9. Export user data (GDPR)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/export
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 10. Delete account (DESTRUCTIVE — run last)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/auth/account
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
